data.title: Worst soup ever
data.text: Should have drank the salt shaker instead as it would have been less salty.  Sub was poor as well.  Not returning.

data.title: Cute little sub shop
data.text: This place has a line every lunch hour, because it's across the street from the Roshek building. They have great soup all winter long, and you can get any sub as a wrap in as small as a 3" size, perfect for the lighter eater, or as a salad. Try the meatball sub (served, inexplicably, with lettuce, tomato, onion, and pickle), or the "breakfast" wrap with egg salad, bacon, and cheese. The soups vary every day, and the macaroni and cheese soup is the best!
